140499666.description:
Buy 12":

http://shop.fadetomind.net/product/mind001-mikeq-dj-sliink

Buy Digital:
https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/mind-to-mind-single/id854113033
http://boomkat.com/downloads/984455-mikeq-dj-sliink-mind-to-mind-mikeq-dj-sliink

Mind to Mind is a new release series created by Fade to Mind focused on new and unprecedented collaborations between producers, vocalists, artists, and designers.

MIND TO MIND: MIKEQ & DJ SLIINK, the first in Fade to Mind’s new collaboration-based release series, brings together two of New Jersey’s living legends, Ballroom innovator MikeQ and Club god DJ Sliink.  The two producers first connected in 2011, leading to Sliink’s remix of MikeQ’s The Ha Dub Rewerk’d.  This new collaborative release picks up from where MikeQ’s last Fade to Mind EP left off, blending elements of ballroom and jersey into two vicious tracks equally at home on the runway or at a rave. The Bitch spins Miss Jay’s classic vocals into an acid frenzy, while Werk’d It is propelled by dramatic chops and frenzied stabs that screams feminine destruction on the dancefloor.

In MikeQ’s own words, “Both tracks have Jersey Club And Ballroom Elements, and come from deep within both scenes.”  Trading versions back and forth, MikeQ and Sliink found a shared language, adding their own touches to connect both styles into a release that looks to the future of both genres and celebrates the creative explosion of club production coming out of New Jersey today.

94276269.title: Kingdom - Viper XL (Preview)
94276269.description:
Out Now on Fade to Mind:
https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/vertical-xl/id642960740

http://fadetomind.net/music/eps/vertical-xl/

Vertical XL is Kingdom’s 5th EP, a personal body of work made during his first years living in Los Angeles. The seven tracks chart a wide emotional terrain, connecting recent developments in Kingdom’s production with seminal darker influences. Drawing its stories from moonlit rural isolation and dissonant moments in club vortexes, Vertical XL is a definitive insight into Kingdom’s journey as an artist, steeped in elements of grime, jungle, and R&B.

On the euphoric / cathartic lead single "Bank Head (featuring Kelela)", Fade to Mind's new vocalist Kelela completes Kingdom’s new vision of R&B, marking the first release in a series of upcoming collaborations between the two. From love to loss, the fresh romance of "Zip Line" gives way to the dark rap mortality of "Corpse". The grime-influenced "Viper Lash" is designed to rattle the club, an abstract dancefloor weapon with ominous bass explosions and spattered percussion. Completing the EP are "Takedown Notice", a slow-grinding bedroom ballad, and the anthemic build of "Viper XL".

112089805.title: I Run This Club (prod. Siyoung)
112089805.description:
MOM010: Cakes Da Killa - I Run This Club // OUT NOW!!
BUY - itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-run-t…b-ep/id690909950

Stream: Cakes Da Killa - I Run This Club (Original Mix) via PITCHFORK - pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/160…7-i-run-this-club/

"The most clinically insane cunt bitch up in the game" is back with a step by step guide for club domination. Learn how to run this club, the Cakes Da Killa way. Whether it's a country club, Sam's club, or da club (as heard in 50 Cent's "In Da Club"), Cakes will show you how to turn up and TURN UP.

------------------------------------

Early support from: Jamie Lidell, Drop The Lime, Distal, MikeQ, Starkey, Shiftee, Vjaun Allure, Reid Speed, Chrissy Murderbot, Proper Villains, Rx, Nick Hook, Glacial Sound, Pawn, JBeatz, Blaze Tripp, Brent Still Life, Sonkin, and more.

------------------------------------

From Pitchfork:
"With "I Run This Club", self-described "most clinically insane cunt bitch up in the game" Cakes Da Killa offers yet another demented banger in the form of "Goodies"-- only, this time he swapping out the nitrous-balloon giddiness of that song for something much darker. If “Goodies” is what you’d hear at the glitzy, glittery discotheque of your dreams, “I Run This Club” is what the DJ’s spinning at the grimier, better party in the basement. Philly bass producer Siyoung's beat is a relentless minimalist assemblage of syncopated kick drum, vocal loops, and siren-like synths, and Cakes attacks it with an appropriately aggro flow, spitting with the kind of assuredness that suggests he’s living up to the potential that his debut mixtape The Eulogy strongly hinted at. “I Run This Club” drops September 16 on DJ Shiftee’s Hot Mom USA label."

------------------------------------

Artwork by Max Bode, Field Trip World.
Mastered by Luca "Digital Boy" Pretolesi.

84616284.title: Egyptrixx - Liberation front MikeQ Remix - Bok Bok Re-Edit
84616284.description:
This installement of the NSWL series is dedicated to “Liberation Front” taken from Egyptrixx’ debut LP “Bible Eyes”.

On the A side, the original track is taken on by DJ Mike Q, a stalwart of the vogue / ballroom scene of his native New Jersey. Mike delivers an incredibly raw and stripped down version, re-working Egyptrixx’s unique sound design into a matrix of hard kicks, runway percussion and the of course the ballroom genre’s Masters At Work-sampling dramatic HA snare. An uncompromising rhythm track, this is club music at its most direct.

The A side also features an edit of Mike Q’s remix by Bok Bok, re-arranging the track and adding a big acid bassline to bring that soundsytem weight.

Meanwhile keeping DJs happy, the B side is dedicated to the original mix of “Liberation Front” in its full 45rpm seven-minute glory.

145898966.description:
Buy 12":
http://boomkat.com/vinyl/963951-mikeq-dj-sliink-mind-to-mind-mikeq-dj-sliink
http://shop.fadetomind.net/product/mind001-mikeq-dj-sliink

Buy Digital:
https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/mind-to-mind-single/id854113033

Mind to Mind is a new release series created by Fade to Mind focused on new and unprecedented collaborations between producers, vocalists, artists, and designers.

MIND TO MIND: MIKEQ & DJ SLIINK, the first in Fade to Mind’s new collaboration-based release series, brings together two of New Jersey’s living legends, Ballroom innovator MikeQ and Club god DJ Sliink. The two producers first connected in 2011, leading to Sliink’s remix of MikeQ’s The Ha Dub Rewerk’d. This new collaborative release picks up from where MikeQ’s last Fade to Mind EP left off, blending elements of ballroom and jersey into two vicious tracks equally at home on the runway or at a rave. The Bitch spins Miss Jay’s classic vocals into an acid frenzy, while Werk’d It is propelled by dramatic chops and frenzied stabs that screams feminine destruction on the dancefloor.

In MikeQ’s own words, “Both tracks have Jersey Club And Ballroom Elements, and come from deep within both scenes.” Trading versions back and forth, MikeQ and Sliink found a shared language, adding their own touches to connect both styles into a release that looks to the future of both genres and celebrates the creative explosion of club production coming out of New Jersey today.
